cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about improving the translation quality of neural machine translation (NMT) systems, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates the technique on the basis of BLEU score, which is a common metric used in NMT research, indicating that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves preprocessing the input, which is a common technique in information retrieval (IR), suggesting that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
